==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*dora-''. Cognate with Old Saxon ''dor'', Old High German [[tor]] (German [[Tor]] ‘gate’), Gothic [[𐌳𐌰𐌿𐍂]]. The Germanic word also existed in different stem-endings: ''*duru-'' (see Old English [[duru]]), ''*duri-'' (see German [[Tür]]). Indo-European cognates include Greek [[θυρα]], Latin [[foris]], Lithuanian [[durys|dùrys]], Old Church Slavonic [[двьрь]] (Russian [[дверь]]).

===Pronunciation===
